President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Hala Y. Jarbou of Michigan as Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Michigan. Jarbou currently serves as a Judge on Michigan's Sixth Judicial Circuit and previously worked as an Assistant United States Attorney, prosecuting cases involving drug and firearms offenses, child pornography, and high-level drug trafficking. She also served as an Assistant Prosecuting Attorney in the Oakland County Prosecutor's Office, prosecuting general felony offenses, homicides, child sexual assault, and high profile felony cases. Jarbou holds a B.B.A. from the University of Michigan and a J.D. from Wayne State University Law School.

Additionally, Gregory S. Tabor of Arkansas has been nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the Western District of Arkansas. Tabor is currently the Chief of Police at the Northwest Arkansas National Airport and previously served for 34 years with the City of Fayetteville, Arkansas Police Department, retiring as the Chief of Police in 2019. He was also the Chairman of the Board for the Fourth Judicial District Drug Task Force. Tabor earned his Police Officer Certificate from the Arkansas Law Enforcement Training Academy.